        "subject": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)",
        "message": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)\n\nThis patch does a lot of fixes and cleanup:\n- grab an inode refcount by top cl_object, so that it can't go away\n- cl_object now can be purged by shrinker\n- change the way to create cl_object, now it will be created\nin ll_file_open and ll_setattr_ost\n- cleanup the code by defining cl_object_kill\n\nFuture work:\n- now pages and locks are holding a refcount against cl_object, this causes\ncl_objects can't be purged by shrinker if there exists pages and locks\nfor an object. This is very bad, it needs fixing.\n- lu_object cache algo. The current alogrithm is not good, it should be working\nas the following:\n* if the object is in use, don't put it into LRU list\n* when the last reference of object is put, put it into LRU\n* fairness of LRU - LRU is tightly coupled with hash in current\nimplementation, must fix.\n- lu_obj_hop_put needs revising.\n\nChange-Id: I6780d6efff05d4d9dca220ce4aaa43994f38a954\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jay@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
